<th>Finding Right</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>General Upper Limbs (Anterior/Posterior)</td>
<td>Redness, swelling, sign of injury, scar mark of previous surgery,
            deformity, muscle wasting, muscle bulk. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=233s">3:53</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=248s">4:08</a>) </td>
<td><br/>
</td>
<td><br/>
</td>
<td>Video states patient's muscle bulk "used to be normal" and "no
            deformity, no scar mark".</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h4>PALPATION (Specifically for Tone in the video context for Upper Limbs)</h4>
<p><em>Note: The video primarily demonstrates tone assessment for the upper
        limbs under "palpation." Tenderness palpation was shown for the neck.</em></p>
<table border="1" style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse;">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Test</th>
<th>Finding Left</th>
<th>Finding Right</th>
<th>Notes (Video Time)</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Tone</strong> (Assessed by passive movement at elbow and
            wrist)</td>
<td><br/>
</td>
<td><br/>
</td>
<td>Patient asked to relax. Examiner performs passive
            flexion/extension at elbow and wrist. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=250s">4:10</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=275s">4:35</a>) </td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h4>NEUROLOGICAL EXAMINATION</h4>
<h3>Sensory System:</h3>
<p><em>Modalities: Fine Touch (Cotton Wool), Pain Touch (Neuro Pin/Sharp
        object).</em></p>
<p><em>Key: N = Normal (Intact), R = Reduced, A = Absent. (Patient says
        "yes" when felt).</em></p>
