</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p><em>(End of Upper Limb Neurological Examination as shown in video for
        Whiplash/Brachial Plexus context)</em></p>
<h3>NECK EXAMINATION (Whiplash Context)</h3>
<h4>INSPECTION</h4>
<table border="1" style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse;">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Area / Aspect</th>
<th>Observation Points (Video Time)</th>
<th>Findings</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>General Neck (Anterior/Posterior/Lateral)</td>
<td>Redness, swelling, sign of any injury, scar mark of previous surgery, deformity.
                (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=40s">0:40</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=49s">0:49</a>)
              </td>
<td></td>
<td>Video states for the patient: "no redness, no swelling, no sign of any injury, no scar mark of the previous surgery or deformity."</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h4>PALPATION</h4>
<table border="1" style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse;">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Test</th>
<th>Technique / Area Palpated (Video Time)</th>
<th>Finding (Tenderness Present/Absent)</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Spinal Tenderness (Spinous Processes)</td>
<td>Palpation down the spinous processes.
                (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=62s">1:02</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=75s">1:15</a>)
              </td>
<td></td>
<td>Patient to report any pain.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Paraspinal Tenderness</td>
<td>Palpation of paraspinal muscles, can be done in a zigzag manner, one side at a time.
                (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=75s">1:15</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=93s">1:33</a>)
              </td>
<td></td>
<td>Video notes patient showed tenderness in the right paraspinal area. (Example: "Tenderness noted right paraspinal C3-C5")</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h4>RANGE OF MOTION (NECK MOVEMENTS)</h4>
<p><em><b>Important Prerequisite:</b> Before proceeding with neck movements, ensure the neck is stabilized if any suspicion of instability. Cervical spine X-rays should be confirmed as normal if trauma is involved or there are red flags.
          (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=402s">6:42</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=414s">6:54</a>)
        </em></p>
<table border="1" style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse;">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Movement</th>
<th>Instruction to Patient (Video Time)</th>
<th>Observed Outcome (e.g., Full, Restricted, Painful)</th>
<th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>Flexion</td>
<td>"Touch your chin with your chest."
                (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=420s">7:00</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=425s">7:05</a>)
              </td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Extension</td>
<td>"Look up at the ceiling."
                (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=425s">7:05</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=428s">7:08</a>)
              </td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Lateral Rotation (Right)</td>
<td>"Look at your right side."
                (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=432s">7:12</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=436s">7:16</a>)
              </td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Lateral Rotation (Left)</td>
<td>"Okay, your left side."
                (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=436s">7:16</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=438s">7:18</a>)
              </td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>Lateral Flexion (Right)</td>
<td>"Try to touch your right ear with your right shoulder."
                (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=440s">7:20</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=443s">7:23</a>)
              </td>
<td></td>
