                (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=447s">7:27</a> - <a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sEhVgHRObQ4&amp;t=449s">7:29</a>)
              </td>
<td></td>
<td></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<h4>III. DIAGNOSIS &amp; MANAGEMENT DISCUSSION</h4>
<ol>
<li><strong>Likely Diagnosis:</strong> Whiplash Injury. (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p4GHGCM_aiM&amp;t=653s">10:53</a>)
        <ul>
<li><em>Explain: "Based on how the accident happened and your symptoms
              starting a few hours later, along with the tenderness in the
              muscles beside your spine and restricted neck movements (if
              C-spine cleared and movements tested), it's most likely a whiplash
              injury. The X-ray (if done) being normal also supports this, as
              whiplash is a soft tissue injury."</em></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Management Plan:</strong>
<ul>
<li><strong>Keep Neck Mobile:</strong> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p4GHGCM_aiM&amp;t=672s">11:12</a>)
            <ul>
<li>"The most important part of treatment is to keep your neck
                mobile, even if it's a bit painful. Not moving it can make it
                stiffer and more painful in the long run."</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Pain Relief:</strong> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p4GHGCM_aiM&amp;t=678s">11:18</a>)
            <ul>
<li>"We can provide you with stronger painkillers to help manage
                the discomfort and allow you to move your neck." (e.g.,
                paracetamol, ibuprofen, co-codamol if appropriate).</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Physiotherapy Referral:</strong> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p4GHGCM_aiM&amp;t=707s">11:47</a>)
            <ul>
<li>"I'll also refer you to a physiotherapist. They can give you
                specific exercises to help with pain and restore movement."</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Ice Compression:</strong> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p4GHGCM_aiM&amp;t=712s">11:52</a>)
            <ul>
<li>"You can try applying ice packs. Wrap some ice in a towel and
                apply it to your neck for 10-15 minutes, a couple of times a
                day. Don't apply ice directly to the skin."</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Neck Collar:</strong>
<ul>
<li>"We generally advise against using a neck collar for whiplash,
                as it can make the neck stiffer. Keeping it mobile is key." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p4GHGCM_aiM&amp;t=733s">12:13</a>)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Prognosis &amp; Timeframe:</strong>
<ul>
<li>"It's important to know that whiplash injuries can take some
                time to get better, sometimes a few weeks or even a few months.
                It's a time-consuming process." (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p4GHGCM_aiM&amp;t=761s">12:41</a>)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Steroids:</strong> <em>(Mentioned as rare, later option
              if pain is severe - likely not first-line in OSCE).</em> (<a class="timestamp" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p4GHGCM_aiM&amp;t=755s">12:35</a>)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Safety Netting / Red Flags for Patient to Watch For:</strong>
<ul>
<li>Worsening pain not controlled by painkillers.</li>
<li>Development of new numbness, tingling, or weakness in arms or
            legs.</li>
<li>Problems with bladder or bowel control.</li>
<li>Severe headache, dizziness, or visual disturbances.</li>
<li>"If any of these occur, please seek medical attention promptly."</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><strong>Address Patient Concerns (ICE):</strong>
<ul>
<li>"Do you have any particular concerns or questions about this?"</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<script>
            document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
            const timestampLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.timestamp');
            
            timestampLinks.forEach(link => {
                link.addEventListener('click', function(event) {
                    event.preventDefault(); // Prevent the default link navigation
                    const href = this.getAttribute('href');
                    let seconds = null;
                    let videoId = null;
                    
                    // Extract video ID from the YouTube URL
                    const videoIdMatch = href.match(/(?:youtube\.com\/watch\?v=|youtu\.be\/)([a-zA-Z0-9_-]+)/);
                    if (videoIdMatch && videoIdMatch[1]) {
                        videoId = videoIdMatch[1];
                    }
                    
                    // Try to extract time from 't=XXs' format
                    const timeMatchSeconds = href.match(/t=(\d+)s?/); // Made 's' optional
                    if (timeMatchSeconds && timeMatchSeconds[1]) {
                        seconds = timeMatchSeconds[1];
                    } else {
                        // Fallback: Try to extract from '?start=XX' or '&start=XX'
                        const timeMatchStart = href.match(/[?&]start=(\d+)/);
                        if (timeMatchStart && timeMatchStart[1]) {
                            seconds = timeMatchStart[1];
                        }
                    }
                    
                    if (videoId && seconds !== null) {
                        // Find all iframes that contain YouTube embeds
                        const allIframes = document.querySelectorAll('iframe[src*="youtube.com/embed"]');
                        
                        // Find the iframe that matches this video ID
                        let targetIframe = null;
                        allIframes.forEach(iframe => {
                            const iframeSrc = iframe.src;
                            if (iframeSrc.includes(videoId)) {
                                targetIframe = iframe;
                            }
                        });
                        
                        if (targetIframe) {
                            // Extract the base embed URL from the current iframe src
                            const baseEmbedUrl = `https://www.youtube.com/embed/${videoId}`;
                            
                            // Construct the new URL for the iframe to start at the specific time and autoplay
                            targetIframe.src = `${baseEmbedUrl}?start=${seconds}&autoplay=1&rel=0`;
                            // rel=0 attempts to prevent related videos from other channels at the end
                        } else {
                            console.warn(`Could not find iframe for video ID: ${videoId}`);
                        }
                    } else {
                        console.warn("Could not parse video ID or time from link: " + href);
                    }
                });
            });
        });

    </script>
    <script src="theme-toggle.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
